                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Sidur for the entire year, rite of Aleppo</summary>
                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Marsh_90_a">
                            <locus>ff. 1r-202v</locus>
                            <title>Sidur for the entire year according to the rite of Aleppo (Aram Tsuvah)</title>
                            <title xml:lang="he">  סדור מנהג ארם צובה לכל השנה</title>
                            <note>Compilation of different MSS: 
                            <list>
                                    <item>fols. 1v-122r, 162: [15th century], the name Elijah is pointed out on fol. 73v;</item>
                                    <item>fols. 126-131, 135-145: [14th century?], completed by a later (Persian?) hand on fols. 124-125, 132-134, 146;</item>
                                    <item>fols. 149-161: [ca. 1300?], completed on fols. 147v-148v by the hand of [<persName>Berakhot ben Josef</persName>, Aleppo, ca. 1467-1484, see also MS. Huntington 612];</item>
                                    <item>fols. 163v-202v: [14th century?].</item>
                                </list>
                            </note>
                            <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
